     <font class="TallRed">Another long day in the office.<a name="108785297223922065">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          <div style="align:right; border:1px solid #333333;float:right;padding:5px;background-color:#FFFFFF;"><img src="http://www.devlogik.com/www/E3R_2/blog/1337yo.jpg" /><br />Must...unplug...</div>Man, today I couldn't tell the difference between opportunity and punishment. I accomplished in 3 days what would have taken another intern a month(?) or so and so now everybody jumpin on me to do all kinds of crazy stuff. For example, here is one conversation I had today with the licensing director, who we (for all intensive purposes) will call "F". She is introducing me to another female worker in the licensing department ("K").<blockquote>F: K, this is Joseph Burdick, the new intern for us and media to share.<br />Brain: ooo, goodie-- there's nothing more gratifying than breaking multiple deadlines simultaneously.<br />K: Hello.<br />Me: Hi, nice to meet ya *shakes hand*<br />F: He is said to be fast, efficient, adaptive, and creative.<br />K: Excellent!<br />Brain: coulda fooled me.<br />F: Okay Joseph, here's your mountain of work.<br />Me: HOLY ISHT!<br /><end of conversation as I died instantly from my chest collapsing due to the weight of the paperwork handed over to me by the 40 year old woman.></blockquote>Yeah, wow, I have never seen so many deadlines open at the same time. This, I know now, <em>IS</em> the real world. The other stuff I have done has been the real world as well but, luckily, I was so skilled in those things I foolishly finished them quickly. <br /><br />I actually began to panic at my desk. I sat there, clicking away at various things to find contact information for over 300 people & corporations-- eyes wide and heart pumping. See, when I get to panic in a public area like this, I don't scream, sweat, or cry like most people. No, I start laughing like a mad-man thinking how the _____ am I going to pull this off.<blockquote>Brain: you know, Joe. You're on the 13th floor. You run out of that window across the hall and say bye bye to all of these deadlines!</blockquote>No, wouldn't want to land on anybody or cause a gruesome scene that blocks traffic worse than Reagan's soul chamber. Plus, why would I OFF myself with the <a href="http://developer.apple.com/wwdc/">WWDC</a> right around the corner? Oh well, the plan is to start on the right foot tommorrow and start making calls. I promised myself I wouldn't post very much here right now since I'm so pooped but damned if I didn't. <br /><strong>Things I could crap on today:</strong> misinformation on unwritten private computer & network policies. If I get another message as to what I can and can't do in my office, I'm going to walk in on Friday with my 500lbs SCSI Raid system, turn the bitch on and take out all of the power in Washington D.C. Hoo<em>ha</em>!<br /><strong>Things I could smile about today:</strong> <a href="http://www.pcworld.com/news/article/0,aid,116591,00.asp">news that laptops will soon be powered by fuel cells</a>. Why not just crash your windows machine when you can make it totally explode!<br />
          <div class="byline">
<b>jd.b!</b>&nbsp;@ 5:00 PM [<a href="http://www.devlogik.com/www/E3R_2/blog/2004/06/another-long-day-in-office.php" title="permanent link">#</a>|<a href="mailto:devlogik@gmail.com?subject=RE: E3R POST #108785297223922065&body=Hey jd.b!!">e</a>|<a href="http://www.devlogik.com/www/E3R_2/blog/2004/06/another-long-day-in-office.php">0.</a>cmnt(s)]</div>
		</div><br>


     
     
